# Project Generation Workflow

## Core Function
Create a complete, ready-to-develop project scaffold with CI/CD, docs, and compliance rules.

## `[MUST]` - Execute Generation

### Step 1: List Templates (Optional)
Execute: `python scripts/generate_client_project.py --list-templates | cat`
**Acceptance:** Templates printed without error

### Step 2: Dry Run
Execute: `python scripts/generate_client_project.py --name {{NAME}} --industry {{INDUSTRY}} --project-type {{PROJECT_TYPE}} --frontend {{FRONTEND}} --backend {{BACKEND}} --database {{DATABASE}} --auth {{AUTH}} --deploy {{DEPLOY}} {{#if COMPLIANCE}}--compliance {{COMPLIANCE}}{{/if}} --output-dir ../_generated --workers {{WORKERS|8}} --dry-run --yes --include-cursor-assets`
**Acceptance:** Structure preview printed, no files created, exit 0

### Step 3: Generate
Execute: `python scripts/generate_client_project.py --name {{NAME}} --industry {{INDUSTRY}} --project-type {{PROJECT_TYPE}} --frontend {{FRONTEND}} --backend {{BACKEND}} --database {{DATABASE}} --auth {{AUTH}} --deploy {{DEPLOY}} {{#if COMPLIANCE}}--compliance {{COMPLIANCE}}{{/if}} --output-dir ../_generated --workers {{WORKERS|8}} --yes --force --include-cursor-assets`
**Acceptance:** Project created, expected files exist, exit 0

### Step 4: Validate Rules (Optional)
Execute: `cd ../_generated/{{NAME}} && [ -d .git ] && python .cursor/tools/validate_rules.py && python .cursor/tools/check_compliance.py`
**Acceptance:** Rules OK, compliance rules present

### Step 5: Setup & Run
Execute: `cd ../_generated/{{NAME}} && make setup && make dev`
**Acceptance:** Install succeeds, dev environment starts

## Execution
When triggered, the workflow runs dry-run → generate → validate → setup in order.

